b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Jasper Chat is best suited for marketing teams, brand voice chat, content ideation, campaign planning, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Microsoft Copilot, meanwhile, shines for Office 365 users, enterprise, Windows users, productivity, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Jasper Chat describes itself as \"Marketing-focused AI chat integrated into Jasper platform.\" Microsoft Copilot, established in 2023, positions itself as \"Microsoft's AI assistant integrated across Office 365 and Windows.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Microsoft Copilot** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (9 vs 4), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Jasper Chat is a poor choice — far from it. Jasper Chat excels in its own right, particularly for marketing teams and brand voice chat.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value deep microsoft 365 integration, go with Microsoft Copilot. If trained on marketing best practices matters more to you, Jasper Chat is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
